A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Dr. Terrence J. Roberts; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Dr. Terrence J. Roberts, a distinguished psychologist, educator, and civil rights
3 activist, played a pivotal role in American history as one of the Little Rock Nine, the
4 courageous group of African American students who integrated Central High School in Little
5 Rock, Arkansas, in 1957; and
6 WHEREAS, he has dedicated 40 years to the field of psychology, practicing as a clinical
7 psychologist from 1975 to 2015 in Deer Park and Pasadena, California, while also serving
8 as director of mental health services at St. Helena Hospital and Health Center from 1977 to
9 1985; and
10 WHEREAS, Dr. Roberts has served in higher education as assistant dean of student services
11 at UCLA's School of Social Welfare from 1985 to 1993 and as department chair and faculty
12 member in psychology at Antioch University, Los Angeles, from 1993 to 2008; and
13 WHEREAS, as CEO of Terrence Roberts Consulting, a management consulting firm
14 originally founded as Terrence J. Roberts and Associates in 1975, he has worked to promote
