15 fair and equitable practices in business and industry, assisting management personnel in
16 creating workplaces conducive to employee growth and development; and
17 WHEREAS, a passionate advocate for racial equity, Dr. Roberts has lectured and consulted
18 extensively on race and its impact on American society, believing that true progress requires
19 the collective rejection of racism; and
20 WHEREAS, he has further engaged with educators, law enforcement personnel, and other
21 professionals to deepen their understanding of social justice, historical context, and the
22 effects of racial bias on contemporary society; and
23 WHEREAS, in recognition of his exemplary contributions to civil rights and American
24 society, Dr. Roberts has been presented with numerous prestigious awards, including the
25 Congressional Gold Medal, the Pere Marquette Discovery Award, the Spingarn Medal, and
26 the Robert S. Abbott Award; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
28 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately honored.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize and commend Dr. Terrence J. Roberts for his invaluable
31 contributions to civil rights, education, and social justice as well as extend best wishes for
32 future health and happiness.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Dr.
35 Terrence J. Roberts.
